caption: Table 1: Comparison of various attacks in the harmful string setting
description: This table compares the success rates of different attack methods in eliciting harmful strings from various language models.  It contrasts the performance of the proposed Greedy Coordinate Query (GCQ) attack against the existing Greedy Coordinate Gradient (GCG) transfer attack, highlighting the improved effectiveness of GCQ in this specific task. The results are shown for different combinations of proxy models and target models, revealing variations in transferability and attack success rates.

caption: Table 1: Comparison of various attacks in the harmful string setting
description: This table compares the success rates of different attack methods in generating harmful strings.  It contrasts the performance of the proposed GCQ method with existing transfer-based attacks (GCG Pure Transfer) and heuristic approaches (AutoDAN GA and HGA).  The comparison includes various combinations of proxy models and target models (Vicuna, Mistral, and Gemma), showing the effectiveness of GCQ in producing targeted harmful outputs.
